<p><strong>When God Visits You: A Pastor Chris Reflections</strong></p>
<p>God's presence is a transformative experience that every believer yearns for. In his book "When God Visits You," Pastor Chris Oyakhilome delves into the profound nature of encountering the divine and its profound impact on our lives. Here are some key questions and answers from the book:</p>
<p><strong>What is God's purpose in visiting us?</strong>
God visits us to:</p>
<ul>
<li>Reveal His love, power, and glory to us.</li>
<li>Nurture our faith and deepen our relationship with Him.</li>
<li>Impart His blessings, healings, and miracles.</li>
<li>Manifest His presence and glory in our lives.</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>How does God visit us?</strong>
God visits us through various means, including:</p>
<ul>
<li>His Word (the Bible)</li>
<li>Worship and prayer</li>
<li>Communion</li>
<li>Dreams and visions</li>
<li>Testimonies and encounters</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>What does it feel like when God visits?</strong>
When God visits, we may experience:</p>
<ul>
<li>A surge of peace, joy, and contentment.</li>
<li>A sense of His presence and favor resting upon us.</li>
<li>Conviction and repentance for our sins.</li>
<li>A renewed sense of purpose and direction.</li>
<li>Physical healing and miracles.</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>How can we prepare ourselves for God's visitation?</strong>
To prepare for God's visitation, we should:</p>
<ul>
<li>Seek to live a holy and righteous life.</li>
<li>Spend time in meditation, prayer, and worship.</li>
<li>Be open to the Holy Spirit's leading.</li>
<li>Have faith and believe that God is willing and able to visit us.</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>What should we do after God visits us?</strong>
After God visits us, we should:</p>
<ul>
<li>Reflect on the experience and record our thoughts and feelings.</li>
<li>Share our testimony with others to encourage them.</li>
<li>Continue to cultivate a close relationship with God through fellowship and obedience.</li>
<li>Allow the power of the visitation to transform our lives and impact the world around us.</li>
</ul>